description: This unit is in the heart of vibrant Back Bay and walkable to Fenway. We offer a comfortable home base to experience all that the city has to offer. Surrounded by beautiful brownstone buildings, tree-lined streets, & a bustling shopping and dining scene, & just steps away from popular attractions like Newbury Street, the Prudential Center, and Copley Square. Plus, with world-class museums, historic landmarks, and delicious seafood nearby, you'll have plenty to see and do during your visit.
neighborhood_overview:
With its brownstones, Boston Marathon finish line, shopping on Newbury Street and waterfront views along the Charles River Esplanade, if you only had one day to get to know Boston, you should probably spend it in the Back Bay.

If you head in any direction, you’re likely to hit one of the Back Bay’s beautiful parks, from Copley Square (a grassy plaza shrouded by skyscrapers) to the Charles River Esplanade (Boston’s waterfront haven for runners, cyclists, sailors and other outdoorsy types). The access to outdoor spaces together with the beautiful historic buildings make Back Bay one of the most desirable places to live in the city



Things to do!

Fenway Park - Just a 1/2 mile walk! Check out a Sox game, or concert, or go for a tour of one of America's oldest ballparks.

Hynes Convention Center - .4 mile walk, the perfect spot if you are in town for a convention!

The unit features all the style and luxury you would expect in a new build:
1. Gourmet kitchen

neighborhood_overview:
Explore the city where the new and the old are in constant conversation, where cobbled-stone streets meet glass-enclosed shopping galleries, where The Freedom Trail landmarks stand beside cutting edge restaurants and renowned performance theatres brush shoulders with trendy nightclubs.
You can feast on some of the country's best dim sum in Chinatown, then walk 15 minutes and be at a brewery by the water. You can go spend an afternoon at a world-renowned art museum and wind up at a Sox game that night or start your day strolling the Harvard University campus and end the day taking in a concert at the legendary House of Blues.
Shopping is great fun in Boston. A prime spot for visitors is Faneuil Hall Marketplace and Quincy Market (15 min drive). Faneuil Hall has a large open plaza where kiosks sell gifts and souvenirs and street performers entertain everyone who ambles through. There are lots of indoor and sidewalk restaurants, the tons of kiosks selling walk-while-you-eat food

name: (T1) Cute & Cozy South End Studio
description: When you book our airbnb in the South End, you can be confident that you'll have attentive hosts who are committed to making your stay as comfortable and enjoyable as possible. Located on Tremont Street, our airbnb is within walking distance of numerous restaurants, galleries, and boutiques in this historic and culturally diverse neighborhood. The South End is the perfect base for exploring and a great choice for anyone looking to experience all that the city has to offer.
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Boston's vibrant South End neighborhood! Our airbnb on Tremont Street is the perfect home base for your travels in the city.

The South End is a historic and culturally diverse neighborhood, known for its beautiful Victorian brownstone buildings and tree-lined streets. It's also home to a thriving food and art scene, with numerous restaurants, galleries, and boutiques to explore. The district is home to some of the most eclectic shopping options in the city, like Diseño, a shop specializing in South American furniture. With the neighborhood's easily accessible layout, all of the South End's shopping is within reach for the walker too.

As for attractions, Boston has no shortage of things to do. Check out the Freedom Trail, a 2.5-mile walking tour that takes you through some of the city's most important historical sites, including the Paul Revere House and the Old North Church. Or head to Fenway Park, home of the Red Sox, for a classic baseball game. Other

host_about:
Hello! We are Airbnb Queen! We started hosting a few apartments in 2015 and grew to be a small company with a love for hosting and giving back to our community!  

When Covid struck our world, we were at a standstill! We had to quickly learn and grow to make sure our health and cleaning standards were in line with those of the CDC. We remain dedicated to providing a happy and healthy stay for our amazing guests!

We are partnered with a wonderful non-profit that specializes in providing  housing for families in need of a discounted or free place to stay for the duration of their hospital visits. Most of these stays are for children under going treatment in our amazing Boston Hospitals. We are honored and motivated to helping those in need. If you are here for a hospital related visit, please let us know prior to booking! 

We hope we get the chance to host you!

description: Show up and start living from day one in Boston with this beautiful one bedroom Blueground apartment. You’ll love coming home to this thoughtfully furnished, beautifully designed, and fully-equipped North Station home . (ID #BOS682)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is located near North Station, a major transportation hub on the border of the North and West Ends. It’s just a short walk to countless dining and entertainment options. The station is one of two inbound terminals in the city for Amtrak and MBTA commuter rail trains. The station area shares the same building as TD Garden, which is the home of the Celtics basketball team and the Bruins hockey team. As a major arena it’s also used for other events, such as concerts and performances. Living near North Station means that using public transit to get around during the day, or out of the city for the weekend is easy and efficient.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
In the early 1600s, Mattapan started as community for Native Americans known as the Mattahunt Tribe. At the dawn of 21st century, immigrants traveling in New England found Mattapan to be a "good place to sit." Irish, Jewish, and Haitian immigrants called the neighborhood home. Now, Mattapan is home to a large African American and Caribbean community.
Taken from the city's website.

We welcomed people from all backgrounds.

description: This new 1 bedroom apartment is located in the heart of the Financial District, just a 3 minute walk to Public Transportation.  Fully stocked kitchen has everything you'd need to cook a basic meal.  The unit is accessible by self-check-in via our smart lock system, so you're group will enjoy easy access to everything from this centrally located place.
neighborhood_overview:
The Financial District is downtown’s business nerve center, however has quieted down nicely since many of the offices have not returned 5 day work weeks. What does that mean for your stay? Not-so-crowded walkways among the stately banks, high-rise offices and sleek restaurants. The apartment is a 2 minutes walk to Post Office Square, home to Norman B. Leventhal Park, which is a great spot for some sun and relaxation, sculptural fountain and garden trellises. Within a 10 minute walk is plenty lunch spots and high-end coffee shops. Fancy lounges and one of the best Irish pubs in America draw what's left of the after-work crowds. From May-October the city is vibrant and lively. In the slower seasons it's pretty quiet and calm save for weekends!

A few key local spots to check out:

New England Aquarium, Central Wharf (T: Aquarium)
Boston Common - a 10min walk Northeast
Dooley's Irish Pub - more pints of Guiness per sq ft than any other bar in America

If you're booking for a non-medical stay, a portion of your dollars support our non-profit partners.  We look forward to hosting you!

The neighborhood stands out through the combination of options it offers. Housing many of the cities most well-known office towers, it also offers a wide variety of shopping and dining options. During weekends, established professionals and graduate students, living in the area, head to Newbury Street for upscale shopping and a stroll along the Commonwealth Avenue Mall. The neighborhood is ideal for active, outdoor lovers, as it is only minutes away from the Esplanade and offers ample green space for jogging and biking. North and South Stations are easily accessible by car and public transit, as is the financial district.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

neighborhood_overview:
In the early 1600s, Mattapan started as community for Native Americans known as the Mattahunt Tribe. At the dawn of 21st century, immigrants traveling in New England found Mattapan to be a "good place to sit." Irish, Jewish, and Haitian immigrants called the neighborhood home. Now, Mattapan is home to a large African American and Caribbean community.
Taken from the city's website.

name: Cozy, convenient Back Bay condo.
description: This special place is close to everything, making it easy to plan your visit.  It is central to premier sites including universities,  historic sites,  museums,  Symphony Hall,  Fenway Park,  Newbury Street and Copley Plaza.
host_about:
I am a retired educator.  I like to refer to myself as a retired elementary teacher although I spent the last quarter of my career as an administrator.  But my teaching years were my best.  The daily student teacher interaction, the laughter and frustrations, the little signs of progress, made the work so fulfilling.

I grew up on a very successful produce and dairy farm in Southeastern Massachusetts.  Our main cash crop was tomatoes but we raised all kinds of vegetables.  They were trucked into Boston.  In the winter the dairy supported us.  My childhood exposed me to hard work but also to a love for the outdoors and nature.

Out of college I worked for the Department of Defense as a teacher in their overseas dependents' schools.  I taught in Istanbul and Seville, Spain.  I was able to travel extensively through Europe for three years.

Upon returning to the States I began teaching in Quincy, Massachusetts, where I remained for thirty years.  The last seven years were spent as a principal of an elementary school which has a majority population of Asian students.  I traveled to China one summer to explore my students' heritage and culture.

In the interim I married Joyce Brothers.  Joyce is a case manager for Boston Senior Home Care.  Her passion is cooking and she is a graduate of the Cambridge School of Culinary Arts.

She and I have raised two children.  Our daughter is a school teacher.  Our son, born in Brazil, is a hair stylist.

As a life-long learner I am a proponent of travel.  Whether for pleasure or business,  travel is the portal to understanding.

host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay
Upon arrival, you’ll either be greeted personally by a Blueground team member or given self-check-in instructions. The entire apartment is yours! You’ll enjoy reliable support via email, phone, and our Guest App, where you can request everything from a home cleaning to extra towels. 

We’ll share all details upon confirmation of your stay.

name: (W-12) South End, Stylish Studio! Location!
description: When you book our airbnb in the South End, you can be confident that you'll have attentive hosts who are committed to making your stay as comfortable and enjoyable as possible. Located on Tremont Street, our airbnb is within walking distance of numerous restaurants, galleries, and boutiques in this historic and culturally diverse neighborhood. The South End is the perfect base for exploring and a great choice for anyone looking to experience all that the city has to offer.
neighborhood_overview:
Stroll down the beautiful brownstone-lined streets while capturing views of Boston's tallest buildings from a distance. Some of Boston's best restaurants are scattered around this neighborhood. There are many gems to be found, from jazz clubs to classy bars and restaurants. It is also home to art galleries, interesting boutiques, artsy stores, and SOWA open market during the summer months. The South End is a true find in the city, with a more residential feeling than Back Bay.

Walk down Tremont Street, and then take a turn down side streets and take it all in. Don't forget to bring your camera or phone, as the townhouses and parks you'll pass are picture worthy!!

Hello! We are Airbnb Queen! We started hosting a few apartments in 2015 and grew to be a small company with a love for hosting and giving back to our community!  

When Covid struck our world, we were at a standstill! We had to quickly learn and grow to make sure our health and cleaning standards were in line with those of the CDC. We remain dedicated to providing a happy and healthy stay for our amazing guests!

We are partnered with a wonderful non-profit that specializes in providing  housing for families in need of a discounted or free place to stay for the duration of their hospital visits. Most of these stays are for children under going treatment in our amazing Boston Hospitals. We are honored and motivated to helping those in need. If you are here for a hospital related visit, please let us know prior to booking! 

We hope we get the chance to host you!

description: Discover serenity at the South End Sanctuary, a charming first-floor studio nestled between the desirable Back Bay and South End neighborhoods. This quaint hideaway offers a private bathroom, mini fridge, oven, cabinets, and closet, all meticulously arranged within its 326 sqft of space. Immerse yourself in the fascinating history of this early 1900s Lodging House while savoring its timeless charm in a central location. Indulge in a tranquil experience in this hidden treasure.
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located on the southeastern border of the Back Bay neighborhood, bordering the South End and just across Massachusetts Avenue from Northeastern University. This little micro-neighborhood is 8 blocks east to west, and its boundaries are Huntington Avenue, Copley Place, the Southwest Corridor Park and Massachusetts Avenue.
The area was formed during a large-scale reclamation of Boston marsh lands back in the early nineteenth century. The area is central to restaurants, coffee shops, bars, but still has a safe quiet residential feel. There's quiet areas for reading, walking a dog, or playing tennis, basketball, or hanging on the lawns at the Southwest Corridor Park. You'll be able to enjoy the benefits of easy access to restaurants, pubs, bars, coffee shops and live music nearby, while enjoying the peace and quiet of a comfortable residential neighborhood.

neighborhood_overview: JP neighborhood is full of Victorian houses and it’s the greenest Boston’s neighborhood.
host_about:
I'm originally from Spain but I've been in JP for almost 26 years when work and study brought me to Boston.  I love traveling and exploring different cultures.  I also love being outdoors especially riding my bike around town or walking my very friendly small dog, Henri.  He is hypoallergenic and he does not shed.  He lives on the second floor but if you met him you'd want him to visit you.  Henri is adorable and lovable!  He is like a teddy bear.
I'm a food enthusiast concentrating on natural and organic foods but I'm not a purist so I'm flexible and adjust to different situations where organic is not available.  I, must say my favorite food is a slice of good bread dipped in olive oil (of course from Spain lol).
I can offer a warm and comforting atmosphere, a home away from home.   I'd be glad to help you to get around the city, where to eat, finding bike paths in the city., etc. 

I have hosted with Air BnB since 2016 with an hiatus in 2019.  I have 17+ years of hosting in my victorian house through various universities in Boston.  I have hosted for short and  long periods many medical researchers, medical visitors, visiting professors, high tech, artists, English learners etc from all over the world.  
House is between Green line (MSPCA stop) and Orange Line (Stony Brook).  Ten min walk to Whole Foods.  My  house is 2 miles to Harvard School of Medicine, Longwood Medical area, Northeastern and a bit further but not far the medical campus of Boston University, 10 min T ride from Back Bay where you can find The Arquitectural School and MFA is 2.3 miles away.

description:
Country living in the city! The space is a very large and sunny guest suite on the first floor with a detached bathroom in a historic house in the heart of Jamaica Plain neighborhood. You will be steps from shops, restaurants, parks, and public transportation.

FRAGRANCE FREE: please note that we are sensitive to perfumes. If you wear highly scented products, our home will not be a good fit :)
neighborhood_overview:
Jamaica Plain is a trendy neighborhood with lots of great dining and shopping options, host to a local art and music scene, and many City of Boston green spaces, all at walking distance from the rental unit. We are located off of JP's Center Street, which is lined with shops and restaurants. Some of Boston's most treasured green spaces - the Arnold Arboretum and Jamaica Plain Pond, are nearby.

For those hoping to explore the rest of Boston via public transportation, the 39 bus stops at the bottom of our street and gets you to Back Bay in 15 minutes. Green Street Station, on the orange line, is a 10 minute walk from the rental unit and a short 15-minute ride to downtown Boston.

name: (T4) Cute Studio in the South End
description: When you book our Airbnb in the South End, you can be confident that you'll have attentive hosts who are committed to making your stay as comfortable and enjoyable as possible. Located on Tremont Street, our Airbnb is within walking distance of numerous restaurants, galleries, and boutiques in this historic and culturally diverse neighborhood. The South End is the perfect base for exploring and a great choice for anyone looking to experience all that the city has to offer.
neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to Boston's vibrant South End neighborhood! Our airbnb on Tremont Street is the perfect home base for your travels in the city.

The South End is a historic and culturally diverse neighborhood, known for its beautiful Victorian brownstone buildings and tree-lined streets. It's also home to a thriving food and art scene, with numerous restaurants, galleries, and boutiques to explore. The district is home to some of the most eclectic shopping options in the city, like Diseño, a shop specializing in South American furniture. With the neighborhood's easily accessible layout, all of the South End's shopping is within reach for the walker too.

As for attractions, Boston has no shortage of things to do. Check out the Freedom Trail, a 2.5-mile walking tour that takes you through some of the city's most important historical sites, including the Paul Revere House and the Old North Church. Or head to Fenway Park, home of the Red Sox, for a classic baseball game. Other
host_about:
Hello! We are Airbnb Queen! We started hosting a few apartments in 2015 and grew to be a small company with a love for hosting and giving back to our community!  

When Covid struck our world, we were at a standstill! We had to quickly learn and grow to make sure our health and cleaning standards were in line with those of the CDC. We remain dedicated to providing a happy and healthy stay for our amazing guests!

We are partnered with a wonderful non-profit that specializes in providing  housing for families in need of a discounted or free place to stay for the duration of their hospital visits. Most of these stays are for children under going treatment in our amazing Boston Hospitals. We are honored and motivated to helping those in need. If you are here for a hospital related visit, please let us know prior to booking! 

We hope we get the chance to host you!

Columbia Point is a remote neighborhood at the edge of a peninsula in Dorchester. While it is within two miles and three subway stops from downtown Boston, it feels cut off from Boston and even the rest of Dorchester. The waterfront neighborhood overlooks Boston Harbor, and is ringed by the scenic Harborwalk, which runs 47 miles along the coast.

Unlike most other neighborhoods of the city, Columbia Point is dominated by large institutional and public housing uses, including the U.Mass Boston campus, Boston College High School, and the Harbor Point mixed-income housing complex. neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located on the southeastern border of the Back Bay neighborhood, bordering the South End and just across Massachusetts Avenue from Northeastern University. This little micro-neighborhood is 8 blocks east to west, and its boundaries are Huntington Avenue, Copley Place, the Southwest Corridor Park and Massachusetts Avenue.
The area was formed during a large-scale reclamation of Boston marsh lands back in the early nineteenth century. The area is central to restaurants, coffee shops, bars, but still has a safe quiet residential feel. There's quiet areas for reading, walking a dog, or playing tennis, basketball, or hanging on the lawns at the Southwest Corridor Park. You'll be able to enjoy the benefits of easy access to restaurants, pubs, bars, coffee shops and live music nearby, while enjoying the peace and quiet of a comfortable residential neighborhood.

neighborhood_overview:
Centrally located in Boston's historic Back Bay on Marlborough Street between Charlesgate East and Massachusetts Avenue (Mass Ave), our condo sits within a short five minute walk from the Hynes Convention Center, the Shops at the Prudential Center and Copley Place Mall, and the boutiques of Newbury and Boylston Street. Our historic Back Bay brownstone is located only one and half blocks from the Charles River Esplanade, and several blocks to the serene Boston Commons and Public Gardens, Fenway Park, the Boston Public Library, historic Beacon Hill, and the Freedom Trail. A corner grocery store is steps away from the building and ample amounts of restaurants and shopping are located around the corner.

The Back Bay neighborhood sits on land reclaimed from water in the mid-nineteenth century. Unlike many other Boston neighborhoods, the Back Bay was laid out in a grid pattern and was based on French urban planning with parks and wide boulevards.

host_about:
I live in the Back Bay and I'm happy to accommodate any unique requests. 

Our properties are available to business professionals seeking short-term corporate housing and families visiting Boston area hospitals.  Please inquire about our special rates for those associated with Shriners, MGH, BWH,  BIDMC, and Mass Eye and Ear. 

My large family are all long-time Boston residents, and most of the members still own apartments from when they lived in downtown Boston.  All of my condo's are owned by members of my family.

Prior to my current job at an investment consulting and advisory firm, where I focus on identifying top-tier real estate managers for our clients to invest in, I worked for a small firm managing a Saudi Prince's hotel investments across North America and Europe.  We managed his interests in the Four Seasons and Fairmont, as well as oversaw his investments in several trophy properties, most notably, NYC's The Plaza; Paris' Four Seasons Hotel George V; and London's The Savoy.  I have taken the same approach we took at my previous firm to managing our personal real estate investments, by providing exceptional service combined with fantastic accommodations in prime locations.

If you stay with us during the summer months (typically available mid weekdays from the middle of June to Labor Day), we'd love to take you out on our 50-ft yacht for a complimentary afternoon sail and lunch (catered by a restaurant / bar we own) around the Boston Harbor (schedule and availability permitting and limited to guests 16 years and older).

Also feel free to inquire about special rates on massages at Bodywaves - a business my father runs on Hanover St. in Boston's Quincy Market / Faneuil Hall area.

Dorchester

A city within a city, full of nuance and pride.
Originally its own municipality, full of large country estates, Dorchester saw a boom in growth during the 1920s when the installation of electric trolley lines made it an appealing destination for the working class. The neighbourhood has become a melting pot, filled with its own nuanced sub-neighborhoods, each with its own unique identities and neighbours who care deeply about their community.

What To Expect:

Everything old is new again.
An alive and thriving neighborhood that lives like a city, bustling with new development and historic restoration.


The Lifestyle:

Boston's most accessible neighborhood, offering something for everyone.

neighborhood_overview:
Centrally located in Boston's historic Beacon Hill on the most popular destination in Beacon Hill (the condo is located on Charles Street), our condo sits steps away from fantastic boutiques and excellent restaurants. Our historic Beacon Hill brownstone is located only a few blocks from the serene Boston Commons and Public Gardens, the Charles River Esplanade, MGH, and the Freedom Trail.

One of Boston's oldest communities and likely Boston's best known neighborhood, Beacon Hill gets its name from a beacon that once stood atop its hill to warn locals about foreign invasion. Approximately one square mile in size, Beacon Hill is bound by Beacon Street, Bowdoin Street, Cambridge Street and Storrow Drive. Its architecture and layout is reflective of old colonial Boston, consisting of brick row houses with beautiful doors, decorative iron work, brick sidewalks, narrow streets, and gas lamps. host_about:
I live in the Back Bay and I'm happy to accommodate any unique requests. 

Our properties are available to business professionals seeking short-term corporate housing and families visiting Boston area hospitals.  Please inquire about our special rates for those associated with Shriners, MGH, BWH,  BIDMC, and Mass Eye and Ear. 

My large family are all long-time Boston residents, and most of the members still own apartments from when they lived in downtown Boston.  All of my condo's are owned by members of my family.

Prior to my current job at an investment consulting and advisory firm, where I focus on identifying top-tier real estate managers for our clients to invest in, I worked for a small firm managing a Saudi Prince's hotel investments across North America and Europe.  We managed his interests in the Four Seasons and Fairmont, as well as oversaw his investments in several trophy properties, most notably, NYC's The Plaza; Paris' Four Seasons Hotel George V; and London's The Savoy.  I have taken the same approach we took at my previous firm to managing our personal real estate investments, by providing exceptional service combined with fantastic accommodations in prime locations.

If you stay with us during the summer months (typically available mid weekdays from the middle of June to Labor Day), we'd love to take you out on our 50-ft yacht for a complimentary afternoon sail and lunch (catered by a restaurant / bar we own) around the Boston Harbor (schedule and availability permitting and limited to guests 16 years and older).

Also feel free to inquire about special rates on massages at Bodywaves - a business my father runs on Hanover St. in Boston's Quincy Market / Faneuil Hall area.

host_about:
I live in Boston and like to do short trips to cities in many countries. I work as a consultant all over the world.
I believe that wasting time is a good thing, we are overscheduled, overinvolved, and overstretched. Traveling allows me to kick back and go to museum just because. Or sit in café, if I am too tired for a museum, or do both.
My favorite city is Barcelona, although Boston great, too, and so is Buxtehude, my home town in Germany. I believe you can find beautiful things in almost all cities, and in the end it is more about whom you travel with and whom you meet. 
My girlfriend and I just started hosting, but already had guests from many parts of the world.

Many wise people have said many wise things. There is a German saying "If you say A, you also have to say B", which is to say that you have to follow through if you have started something. Einstein responded to that: "If you say A, you don't need to say B, you can also see that A was wrong". How about that for humbleness of an atheist. Well, I wasn't there when he said it, but this is what lore has ..
Between my girlfriend and me, we can help you with German, English, French , Chinese, some Spanish and some Japanese. 
We explicitly welcome people from every corner of the world, and everyone who believes in respect and love for all others.

neighborhood_overview:
The North End is Boston's oldest residential neighborhood and could best be described as the "Little Italy" of Boston. The North End is one of the most visited neighborhoods in the City of Boston and is the hub of the Italian-American community. It’s character is woven through the neighborhoods narrow yet vibrant streets that boast some of the best restaurants and old world cafes the City has to offer. And there is history too - Old North Church, Paul Revere's house, burial grounds - seemingly around every corner. The North End is walking distance to so many attractions and is in the middle of everything that the North End is the perfect place to call home for your first trip to Boston or for the seasoned executive looking to be close to the Financial District.

We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. name: Getaway Serenity Suite next to Logan Intl Airport
description:
Our Getaway Serenity Suite is in a great location. We have abundant local dining options within walking distance and are really close to public transit and Logan International Airport. Anything you could possibly need is within walking distance.


Whether you are staying with us for vacation, business, or month-to-month, Serenity Suite Homes provides all the convenience you need.
neighborhood_overview:
The best thing about this neighborhood is that you'll find what you need within walking distance. There are many bodegas on corners, we recommend Savas Market on the corner of Brooks & Bennington (3-minute walk). If you cannot find what you need at the bodegas there is a Shaw's Supermarket that is a 15-minute walk. If you need to do laundry, there are 3 nearby laundromats (5–10-minute walk).

Enjoy the different cuisines around the neighborhood. Our local favorites are MIDA'S (Italian), La Hacienda (Mexican), Angela's Cafe (Mexican & great for breakfast/brunch), Rincon Limeno (Peruvian), Oliveira's Brazilian Steakhouse, and Smoke Shop BBQ. We also have a few cocktail bars that do not disappoint.

Other stores/services you may be interested in that you will find within walking distance are CVS, Walgreens, Marshalls, Nail Salons, Beauty Salons, and Barbershops.

name: Vibrant South End Studio
description: Discover blissful tranquility in the South End Blissful Studio, situated on the second floor of a charming historic brownstone. This thoughtfully arranged micro studio apartment features a full private bathroom, mini fridge, oven, cabinets, and closet all within its cozy 303 sqft. Immerse yourself in the captivating history of this early 1900s residence, once a Lodging House offering short-term stays, and savor its enduring allure. Indulge in the serene ambiance of this delightful urban retreat.
neighborhood_overview:
This apartment is located on the southeastern border of the Back Bay neighborhood, bordering the South End and just across Massachusetts Avenue from Northeastern University. This little micro-neighborhood is 8 blocks east to west, and its boundaries are Huntington Avenue, Copley Place, the Southwest Corridor Park and Massachusetts Avenue.
The area was formed during a large-scale reclamation of Boston marsh lands back in the early nineteenth century. The area is central to restaurants, coffee shops, bars, but still has a safe quiet residential feel. There's quiet areas for reading, walking a dog, or playing tennis, basketball, or hanging on the lawns at the Southwest Corridor Park. You'll be able to enjoy the benefits of easy access to restaurants, pubs, bars, coffee shops and live music nearby, while enjoying the peace and quiet of a comfortable residential neighborhood

host_about:
Hello! We are Airbnb Queen! We started hosting a few apartments in 2015 and grew to be a small company with a love for hosting and giving back to our community!  

When Covid struck our world, we were at a standstill! We had to quickly learn and grow to make sure our health and cleaning standards were in line with those of the CDC. We remain dedicated to providing a happy and healthy stay for our amazing guests!

We are partnered with a wonderful non-profit that specializes in providing  housing for families in need of a discounted or free place to stay for the duration of their hospital visits. Most of these stays are for children under going treatment in our amazing Boston Hospitals. We are honored and motivated to helping those in need. If you are here for a hospital related visit, please let us know prior to booking! 

We hope we get the chance to host you!

name: Blueground | South End, gym, w/d, nr groceries
description: Feel at home wherever you choose to live with Blueground. You’ll love this sophisticated South End furnished one bedroom apartment with its modern decor, fully equipped kitchen, and cheery living room with great views. Ideally located, you’re close to all the best that Boston has to offer! (ID #BOS1022)
neighborhood_overview: This furnished apartment is situated in the South End. It is a diverse and family-friendly neighborhood within range of the Prudential Center and Back Bay skyline. Families love to settle in one of the classic Victorian houses, as there are five public schools in the area. It also attracts artists as it is home to cultural institutions such as the Calderwood Pavilion. The South End has also earned a reputation as one of Boston’s culinary hubs, with close proximity to tons of great restaurants. On weekends residents enjoy brunch and coffee until the late afternoon. South Station is only 12 minutes away by train and the nearest transit is OL.
host_about:
We’re Blueground, a global proptech company with several thousand move-in-ready apartments in a growing number of major cities around the world. With flexible terms and homes in vibrant, centrally based neighborhoods, you’ll feel at home and free to roam for as long as you want — a month, a year, or longer. 

Each apartment is thoughtfully designed with exclusive furnishings, fully equipped kitchens, and incredible amenities – making every day a five-star experience. From day one, you’ll enjoy high-speed Wi-Fi, premium linens, and smart home entertainment. Plus, access to pools, gyms, and outdoor spaces in select buildings.

Why stress over your apartment? We provide a hassle-free alternative — a consistent, quality guest experience that starts even before you arrive. Because we let you book our most up-to-date apartment listings online, confirm with a click, pay securely, and check in easily. 

Even better? You can enhance your stay with car rentals, grocery delivery, laundry services, and more through our special partnerships. 

During your stay

The South End of Boston is one of the city's most vibrant neighborhoods, making it an ideal place to settle for the week!

Located on Mass Ave in Chester Square, your stay at The Chester offers easy access to exploring Boston, including the local bus, Mass Ave T stop off the Orange Line, and Silver Line on Washington Street—perfect for exploring.

The area is known for its exceptional dining, with top restaurants including favorites just outside your door like SRV and Mida.

The neighborhood also boasts a rich cultural scene with numerous art galleries and the Boston Center for the Arts. Beautiful green spaces like the Southwest Corridor Park and historic Victorian architecture add to the charm.

Additionally, you'll have easy access to the Boston Marathon finish line, Boston Medical Center, Boston Public Garden, Fenway Park, Newbury Street, the Prudential Center, and more.

host_about: Thatch is an ever-evolving hospitality management company that specializes in co-living, hotels and apartment-hotels for short and long stays.
